# Patch 0022 — Kavacha layout engine: apply the layout document live
# (ROADMAP Phase 3 "Layout engine applies layout JSON live"; ADR 0008).
#
# WHAT: KavachaLayoutEngine.sys.mjs reads a per-profile kavacha-layout.json
# (schema: customization/layout-engine/layout.schema.json) and applies it to
# browser chrome without a restart — tab orientation, interface density,
# sidebar side/width, hidden elements, per-component sizes. The document
# round-trips with the future about:studio GUI and is hand-editable.
#
# WHY NOT A PREF/OVERLAY: the mapping from one JSON document to several chrome
# surfaces (a pref + root attributes + a generated per-window sheet), plus
# live re-application and file persistence, is logic, not a static default —
# it needs a module. It reuses existing mechanisms wherever it can: tabStyle
# is just the `zen.tabs.vertical` pref (Zen + patch 0010 already react to it),
# and the generated sheet uses the same per-window windowUtils AUTHOR_SHEET
# path as patch 0012. The CSS layer (kavacha-layout.inc.css) is %include'd and
# gated on non-default attribute values, so it is a no-op at the shipped look.
#
# RUNTIME SHAPE (shared with 0023's theme engine): process singleton init()
# installs a pref observer on kavacha.layout.revision (the content->chrome
# doorbell a content page like about:studio bumps), per-window applyToWindow()
# runs from ZenStartup, applyToAllWindows() enumerates navigator:browser on
# change — the KavachaTabMemory (singleton) + KavachaUniversalSearch
# (per-window) pattern.
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED: authored without a local Zen checkout
# (browser/zen-upstream is fetched by build/bootstrap.sh). The modified-file
# hunks are reconstructed against the post-0021 tree; run
# `git -C browser/zen-upstream apply --check` and a Marionette pass before
# marking the ROADMAP item verified. Touches: zen-command-palette.ftl,
# src/zen/common/moz.build, ZenStartup.mjs, zen-theme.css,
# KavachaCommandRegistry.sys.mjs; adds KavachaLayoutEngine.sys.mjs +
# kavacha-layout.inc.css. Applies on top of 0021.
